company_summary:
Tencent Holdings is China based Multi-National Investment Conglomerate Company. Tencent is a leading provider of Internet value added services in China. Headquarters is in China.
Tencent is mainly into businesses related to Video Games, Online Games, Social Media, eCommerce, Payment Systems.

Tesla is USA based Electric Automobile company, Solar Panels, Battery cells, Energy Storage Products manufacturing company and they manufacture Electric Cars, Electric Batteries, Solar Panels & Clean Energy Storage. Tesla is a company of Elon Musk who is owner of SpaceX and this SpaceX is capable of sending rockets to moon privately. Tesla is World's Famous company in manufacturing electric cars at affordable price. Headquarters is in USA.
As on July-30-2023, Tesla market cap was 844 Billion USD and it is World Top 7th company by market cap.

Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSMC) is the world’s largest semiconductor company with headquarters in Taiwan.
As on July-30-2023, TSMC market cap was 523 Billion USD and it is World Top 10th company by market cap.
TSMC deployed 281 distinct process technologies, and manufactured 11,617 products for 510 customers in 2020.

Walmart is World's biggest retail market company and it has eCommerce business as well along with brick and mortar Retail stores. Around the world as on Jan-2022, 2.3 million employees are working for Walmart. In the U.S., where about 90% of the population lives within 10 miles of a Walmart store or Sam’s Club. Headquarters is in USA.

JPMorgan Chase is one of the oldest financial institutions in the United States With a history dating back over 200 years.
JPMorgan Chase is a leading global financial services firm with assets of $2.6 trillion.
JPMorgan have a presence in over 100 markets.
Headquarters is in USA.
As on 2022, JPMorgan Chase has 293,723 employees.
JPMorgan Chase annual revenue generated for period ending Dec-2022 was 128.69 billion USD.

Nvidia Corporation is famous for Graphics, 3D Graphics Cards and Drivers. Nvidia is leading the way in AI computing. Nvidia GPUs simulate human intelligence powering systems that can perceive and understand the world. 
As on July-30-2023, Nvidia Corporation market cap was 1.15 Trillion USD and it is World Top 6th company by market cap.

LVMH group manufacture luxury goods and quality products in five major sectors of the luxury market:  Wines & Spirits, Fashion & Leather Goods, Perfumes & Cosmetics, Watches & Jewelry and Selective Retailing. LVMH has 150,000 employees as on 2021 across the world and reported sales of 53.65 billion euros in 2019.

Procter & Gamble Company is one of World's top FMCG Company with Baby Care, Fabric Care, Family Care, Feminine Care, Hair Care, Home Care, Grooming, Personal Health Care, Oral Care, Skin and Personal Care Products. Headquarters is in USA.

Eli Lilly is a healthcare and pharmaceutical and is USA based MNC company. Key business areas are Oncology, Bio-Medicines, Diabetes and also Animals Health.and Lilly unites caring with discovery to create medicines that make life better for people around the world. Eli Lilly has 33,815 employees as on 2019. Headquarters is in USA.
Three long-established core values guide Lilly :
Integrity.
Excellence.
Respect for People.

Chevron Corporation is USA based Multi-National Energy Company. Chevron is one of the world’s leading integrated energy companies producing safe, reliable energy now and for the future. It  deliver affordable, reliable and ever-cleaner energy – essential to modern life for billions of people around the world. Headquarters is in USA.
